        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-bottom:12px;">1. Shipping Destinations</h2>
        <p>AB Chem India ships within India and to most international destinations. Some products and destinations are restricted by Indian export-control law (SCOMET, NDPS, Drugs &amp; Cosmetics Act), by destination-country regulation, or by carrier policy on hazardous materials. We will confirm shipability for your specific item/destination at the quotation stage.</p>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">2. Processing Time</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left:20px;">
            <li><strong>Catalog items in stock:</strong> dispatched within <strong>1–3 business days</strong> of order confirmation and receipt of cleared payment.</li>
            <li><strong>Catalog items out of stock or made-to-order:</strong> typically <strong>2–6 weeks</strong>; the actual lead time is confirmed at the quotation stage.</li>
            <li><strong>Custom synthesis:</strong> as per the timeline in the project agreement (commonly 4–16 weeks).</li>
            <li><strong>Documentation orders (CoA, MSDS reissue):</strong> emailed within 1–2 business days.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Business days exclude Sundays and Indian public holidays. Orders placed after 14:00 IST or on a non-business day are processed the next business day.</p>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">3. Domestic Shipping (India)</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left:20px;">
            <li><strong>Carriers:</strong> BlueDart, DTDC, Delhivery, FedEx India, India Post Speed Post or specialist hazmat couriers, selected based on product class and destination pincode.</li>
            <li><strong>Transit time:</strong> typically <strong>2–6 business days</strong> after dispatch.</li>
            <li><strong>Shipping charges:</strong> displayed at checkout or stated on the proforma invoice. Charges depend on weight, dimensions, hazard class, cold-chain requirement and destination.</li>
            <li><strong>Cold-chain &amp; controlled-temperature shipments:</strong> dispatched with gel packs, dry ice or validated thermal shippers as required. Additional packaging charges apply.</li>
            <li><strong>Documentation included:</strong> tax invoice, e-way bill (where applicable), Certificate of Analysis (CoA), Material Safety Data Sheet (SDS) and packing list.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">4. International Shipping</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left:20px;">
            <li><strong>Carriers:</strong> DHL Express, FedEx International, UPS, or freight forwarders for bulk and dangerous-goods consignments.</li>
            <li><strong>Transit time:</strong> typically <strong>5–10 business days</strong> for express air freight after customs clearance from India; sea freight 25–45 days.</li>
            <li><strong>Incoterms:</strong> default is <strong>FCA Hyderabad (Incoterms® 2020)</strong>. Other terms (DAP, DDP, CIF) are available on request and will be stated on the proforma invoice.</li>
            <li><strong>Customs, duties &amp; taxes:</strong> import duties, GST/VAT, customs broker fees and any destination-country charges are the responsibility of the Customer (unless DDP is agreed in writing).</li>
            <li><strong>Export documentation:</strong> commercial invoice, packing list, CoA, SDS, dangerous-goods declaration (where applicable), country-of-origin certificate, and any product-specific certificates (non-animal-origin, GMO-free, etc.) on request.</li>
            <li><strong>Restricted items:</strong> orders containing scheduled drugs, narcotics, psychotropics, dual-use SCOMET items or precursor chemicals will be released only after the necessary licences and No-Objection Certificates are in place.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">5. Hazardous Materials (Dangerous Goods)</h2>
        <p>Many of our products are classified as Dangerous Goods (DG) under IATA / ICAO / IMDG / ADR rules. Such consignments are packed by certified personnel using UN-specification packaging and shipped only via DG-approved carriers. The Customer agrees that:</p>
        <ul style="padding-left:20px;">
            <li>The shipping address is staffed during business hours by personnel competent to receive DG;</li>
            <li>Receiving facilities meet the storage requirements stated on the SDS;</li>
            <li>Any DG surcharge levied by the carrier is payable by the Customer.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">6. Tracking</h2>
        <p>An airway bill / tracking number is emailed to the Customer once the consignment is handed over to the carrier. Tracking links are also visible on your order page when logged in.</p>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">7. Delivery, Inspection &amp; Acceptance</h2>
        <ul style="padding-left:20px;">
            <li>The Customer or an authorised representative must be available at the delivery address to receive the consignment.</li>
            <li>On receipt, please <strong>inspect the outer packaging before signing</strong>. If the carton is damaged, wet, leaking or shows signs of tampering, either refuse the delivery or accept it under written protest and note the damage on the carrier's proof-of-delivery.</li>
            <li>Photograph the packaging immediately and notify us within <strong>48 hours</strong> per the <a href="/refund" style="color:var(--primary);">Refund &amp; Cancellation Policy</a>.</li>
            <li>If two delivery attempts are unsuccessful and the consignment is returned to origin, re-shipment will be at the Customer's cost.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">8. Risk &amp; Title</h2>
        <p>Title to the goods passes to the Customer on full payment. Risk passes to the Customer at the point specified by the agreed Incoterm — by default, when the goods are handed over to the first carrier at our facility in Hyderabad. The Customer is encouraged to insure international consignments; insurance can be arranged by AB Chem on request at the Customer's cost.</p>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">9. Delays Beyond Our Control</h2>
        <p>Stated transit times are estimates from the carrier and are not guaranteed. AB Chem is not responsible for delays caused by carrier disruption, customs inspection, weather, strikes, public-health emergencies, incorrect or incomplete addresses, missing import licences, or other circumstances outside our reasonable control. We will, however, work with the Customer and carrier to expedite resolution.</p>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">10. Address Changes &amp; Reroutes</h2>
        <p>Once a consignment has been dispatched, address changes and reroutes are subject to carrier acceptance and additional fees, which will be billed to the Customer.</p>

        <h2 style="color:var(--primary); margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:12px;">11. Contact</h2>
        <p>For shipping queries, tracking issues or documentation requests, please write to <a href="mailto:connect@abchem.co.in" style="color:var(--primary);">connect@abchem.co.in</a> quoting your order number.</p>
